                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d330">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/7372: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-16T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 16, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. Your 548, December 30, 6 p.m.<note n="54" xml:id="d330fn54">
                        <ref target="frus1941v05#pg_768">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, p. 768</ref>.</note> Some weeks prior to
                    the receipt of your telegram under reference I spoke to other officials here in
                    regard to the advisability of this Government’s extending a large loan to China.
                    After receipt of your telegram I spoke again about the matter. I also
                    recommended to the Secretary of the Treasury that a loan, substantial in amount,
                    be made.</p>
                <p>A few days ago the President took the matter up with the Secretary of the
                    Treasury and I understand that the Secretary of the Treasury has been giving the
                    matter most active consideration and that the Secretary of the Treasury has
                    communicated to T. V. Soong the outline of a specific proposal which Soong is
                    referring to his Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
